psalm.text:
[[Ps 138,1]]I will give thanks to you, O LORD, with all my heart, 
for you have heard the words of my mouth; 
in the presence of the angels I will sing your praise;
[[Ps 138,2]]I will worship at your holy temple 
and give thanks to your name. 

Because of your kindness and your truth; 
for you have made great above all things 
your name and your promise.
[[Ps 138,3]]When I called, you answered me; 
you built up strength within me.

[[Ps 138,6]]The LORD is exalted, yet the lowly he sees, 
and the proud he knows from afar.
[[Ps 138,7]]Though I walk amid distress, you preserve me; 
against the anger of my enemies you raise your hand. 

Your right hand saves me.
[[Ps 138,8]]The LORD will complete what he has done for me; 
your kindness, O LORD, endures forever; 
forsake not the work of your hands.

second_reading.text:
[[Col 2,12]]Brothers and sisters: you were buried with Christ in baptism, in which you were also raised with him through faith in the power of God, who raised him from the dead.
[[Col 2,13]]And even when you were dead in transgressions and the uncircumcision of your flesh, he brought you to life along with him, having forgiven us all our transgressions;
[[Col 2,14]]obliterating the bond against us, with its legal claims, which was opposed to us, he also removed it from our midst, nailing it to the cross.
